================================================================================
PLAN T018: ROBUSTNESS IMPROVEMENT CONCEPTS FOR DESKTOP PET ARCHITECTURE
================================================================================

This document outlines four core architectural improvements aimed at making the 3D 
Desktop Pet application more resilient, failure-proof, and robust against common 
desktop environment edge cases.

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
1. ROBUSTNESS IMPROVEMENT 1: ATOMIC CONFIGURATION WRITING & STATE RECOVERY
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------

* Current Problem:
  Settings are loaded from and saved to configuration files dynamically. If the app 
  is terminated abruptly (e.g., system shutdown, task manager force-kill) during a 
  save operation, the configuration file can become corrupted or empty. On subsequent 
  restarts, JSON/key-value parsing will fail, leading to startup crashes.

* Robust Solution:
  1. Atomic File Writing:
     Instead of writing directly to the target config file, write the new settings to 
     a temporary file (e.g., `settings.tmp`) first. Once the write succeeds, perform 
     a synchronous rename/replace operation (`fs.renameSync`) to overwrite the active 
     configuration.
  2. Memory-Safe Default Fallback:
     Implement a robust validation scheme. If the configuration file is missing, empty, 
     or fails to parse, catch the exception, load a hardcoded default configuration 
     object in memory, and recreate the configuration file automatically.

* Code References:
  - Config reading/writing logic in [renderer.js](file:///c:/Users/space/.gemini/antigravity-ide/scratch/desktop-pet/renderer.js#L1145) 
    and [main.js](file:///c:/Users/space/.gemini/antigravity-ide/scratch/desktop-pet/main.js).

