2. ROBUSTNESS IMPROVEMENT 2: OFF-SCREEN BOUNDARY PROTECTION & DOCKING SNAP
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------

* Current Problem:
  When dragging the pet via IPC (`move-window` event), fast mouse sweeps, frame drops, 
  or monitor configuration changes (e.g., unplugging a second monitor) can place the 
  window entirely off-screen. Once off-screen, the pet is unrecoverable, forcing the 
  user to delete settings files or restart the app.

* Robust Solution:
  1. Screen Boundary Clipping:
     In the `move-window` handler in [main.js](file:///c:/Users/space/.gemini/antigravity-ide/scratch/desktop-pet/main.js#L174), 
     retrieve the current display bounds via Electron's `screen.getDisplayMatching(rect)`.
     Check if the target position puts the window coordinates outside the display's 
     bounds. Clamp the position so that a minimum visible anchor region (e.g., at least 
     50x50 pixels of the pet window) is guaranteed to stay within the display area.
  2. Smart Docking Snap:
     Enable an optional snap threshold (e.g., 15 pixels). When dragging the mascot close 
     to screen margins or the system taskbar, automatically snap the window coordinates 
     flush to the edge.

