3. ROBUSTNESS IMPROVEMENT 3: STEAMWORKS API MOCK INTERFACE FOR OFFLINE RESILIENCE
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------

* Current Problem:
  If the Steam client is closed or offline, `steamClient.init(480)` fails. While this is 
  caught safely via try/catch blocks, later attempts in [renderer.js](file:///c:/Users/space/.gemini/antigravity-ide/scratch/desktop-pet/renderer.js) 
  to dispatch achievements or check user statuses can result in null pointer exceptions 
  if not manually checked.

* Robust Solution:
  1. Complete Mock Layer:
     When the Steamworks API fail to initialize, instantiate a dummy mock interface that 
     implements the exact same method signatures as `steamClient` (e.g., `storeStats()`, 
     `setAchievement()`).
  2. Offline Toasts fallback:
     If the mock layer detects an achievement is unlocked while offline, redirect the IPC 
     call to trigger local in-app custom notification toasts, showing the unlock visual 
     locally instead of failing silently.

* Code References:
  - Steamworks initialization in [main.js](file:///c:/Users/space/.gemini/antigravity-ide/scratch/desktop-pet/main.js#L7-L38).
  - Achievement IPC invocations in [renderer.js](file:///c:/Users/space/.gemini/antigravity-ide/scratch/desktop-pet/renderer.js).

